fmiModelDescription.description: Does a predefined amount of CPU work per unit simulated time. Useful for benchmarking.
fmiModelDescription.author: Lars Tandle Kyllingstad

ScalarVariable.name: work_per_time
ScalarVariable.description: How many work units to do per simulated time unit. This was tuned at some point so that 1 work unit would take 1 ms on the author's machine, but this will of course be heavily machine dependent.

ScalarVariable.name: input
ScalarVariable.description: An input value that will affect the computations (and hence the output) in an unspecified way.

ScalarVariable.name: output
ScalarVariable.description: An output value that emerges in an unspecified way from the computations.
